                    <handDesc>
                       <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                          <seg type="script">15th-16th century script</seg>
                          <date notBefore="1400" notAfter="1599"/>
                          <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                          <desc>
                            The handwriting displays some archaic palaeographical features: 
                            ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line, at least once (<locus target="#15v"/>); 
                             ቆ, ቶ, ዐ, የ, ደ, ጸ have angular shape; 
                             መ and ሠ have sometimes angular loops; 
                             the left stroke of ዘ is sometimes slightly slanted; 
                             the numerals are sometimes written without dashes; 
                             ፪ has angular and not separated loops.
                          </desc>
                          <seg type="rubrication"/>
                       </handNote>
                    </handDesc>
                    
